(125, 4, '25% of TV Shows Never Make It Past Season One [Infographic]', 'http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/businessinsider/~3/h-vxTBzMbBs/percent-of-tv-show-cancellations-after-one-season-2013-5', '<p>In the midst of this week''s network upfronts, 31 of your favorite TV shows <a href="http://www.businessinsider.com/tv-shows-canceled-2013-2013-5" target="_blank">just got canceled</a>.</p> <p>But the axed shows aren''t all that surprising, considering that approximately&nbsp;<span>25% of shows get canceled after their first season.</span></p> <p><a href="http://www.cabletv.com/blog/25-of-tv-shows-never-make-it-past-one-season/" target="_blank">CableTV.com</a> put together the below infographic after compiling data on&nbsp;<span>single-season shows from 1955 to today.</span></p> <p><span>Let''s just say, the A-list didn''t always start out that way.</span></p> <p><img src="http://www.cabletv.com/wp-content/uploads/23880/Canceled-A-History-of-Single-Season-TV-Shows.png?maxX=600" border="0" width="600" /></p> <p>Canceled: Single Season TV Shows &ndash; An infographic by the team at <a href="http://www.cabletv.com/blog/25-of-tv-shows-never-make-it-past-one-season/">CableTV.com</a></p><p><strong>SEE ALSO:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.businessinsider.com/tv-shows-canceled-2013-2013-5" >31 of your favorite TV shows just got canceled ></a></strong></p> <p><p>Please follow <a href="http://www.businessinsider.com/thewire">The Wire</a> on <a href="http://twitter.com/tbithewire">Twitter</a> and <a href="http://facebook.com/businessinsider">Facebook</a>.</p><p><a href="http://www.businessinsider.com/percent-of-tv-show-cancellations-after-one-season-2013-5#comments">Join the conversation about this story &#187;</a></p><img width=''1'' height=''1'' src=''http://businessinsider.com.feedsportal.com/c/34800/f/641403/s/2c1233b0/mf.gif'' border=''0''/><div class=''mf-viral''><table border=''0''><tr><td valign=''middle''><a href="http://share.feedsportal.com/share/twitter/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bus